title: multideconv
text: basic function perform cell type deconvolution using six default methods (quanTIseq, DeconRNASeq, CIBERSORTx, EpiDISH, DWLS, MOMF) nine default signatures (see paper). function accepts either raw counts TPM-normalized counts input (genes SYMBOL). NOTE: plan use CIBERSORTx, must provide credentials (see README details). resulting deconvolution matrix automatically saved Results/ directory. output includes combinations deconvolution features, method-signature-cell type. exclude specific methods signatures, use methods signatures_exclude arguments: speed computation, multideconv supports parallelization. Set doParallel = TRUE specify number workers based system’s resources:
code: bulk = multideconv::raw_counts deconv = compute.deconvolution(raw.counts = bulk,                                 methods = c("Quantiseq", "Epidish",                                             "DeconRNASeq", "DWLS","MOMF"),                                 normalized = TRUE,                                 return = TRUE,                                 file_name = "Tutorial") deconv = compute.deconvolution(raw.counts = bulk,                                 methods = c("Quantiseq", "DeconRNASeq"),                                 normalized = TRUE,                                signatures_exclude = "BPRNACan",                                 return = TRUE,                                 file_name = "Tutorial") deconv = compute.deconvolution(raw.counts = bulk,                                 methods = "DWLS",                                 normalized = TRUE,                                 return = TRUE,                                 file_name = "Tutorial",                                 doParallel = TRUE,                                 workers = 3)

title: Compute deconvolution — compute.deconvolution
text: function calculates cell abundance based cell type signatures using different methods signatures. Methods available Quantiseq, MCP, XCell, CibersortX, EpiDISH, DWLS DeconRNASeq. Provided signatures included signatures based bulk methylation data (7 methods 10 signature total). Signatures present src/signatures directory, user can add signatures adding .txt files folder. Second generation methods perform deconvolution based single cell data also available scRNAseq object provided.
